checkpoint 3
I almost died in due suicide. Although I had thought about it before and hurt a lot with sharp objects, something was different on that day. it was as if I "knew" that now the game was over. I hermetically taped my living room and set up a 9 hours ambient mix, with charcoal melting in a bowl alongside my couch. I had been up all night for almost 5 days from amphetamines, pot and booze in an empty stomach, hoping that my body would be in such a slumber so that the carbon monoxide would eventually finish up the slumber. As I lay down and finally had closed my eyes. There was nothing but emptiness concealed underneath the surface of my mind, while my heart was palpitating with a numb beat. I was waiting there for the epilogue.
Here I am writing this, being grateful to God for his saving me and leading the way to this place. So I pray for all of us and I bless you all by sending you love.

author: ire
text:
Fuck it.

Checkpoint.

It's 2 am. A video of vines on a blue sky with a japanese title appeared in my recommended. I clicked it, and was pleasantly surprised to hear Stickerbrush Symphony from Donkey Kong Country 2. I've listened to video game music for a while and this is one of my favorite songs ever. It's incredible. But the real shocker came from the comments. The vast majority of comments start with "checkpoint" and then proceed to tell some kind of life story, and often end with "GAME SAVED" and then the date the comment was posted.

This was fucking surreal. It was trippy.

A lot of comments say things like "whoever got this in your recommended, you're now a main character of earth." I don't tend to believe in shit like this, but I did a double take. I was taken aback. As I read more comments, my interest was piqued. What the fuck is this video. I don't really buy into the whole thing, so i decide not to leave one of these "checkpoint" comments and instead inform people of what the song is because it doesn't seem a lot of people knew. One guy laughed at the fact it was from a Donkey Kong game, he thought it must have been some kind of orchestral masterpiece. 

It is.

So I go to the channel that posted the music and sort the videos by "popular." I find Gangplank Galleon, another great song. The comments are similar. "Checkpoint," with peoples life story. And now I'm here.

This is confusing as fuck, this is trippy as hell, this is probably the most vividly surreal my life has ever gotten, and if you've read this far I'd like to personally thank you from the bottom of my heart.

As much as you think you're alone, you're not. I won't go into any details or whatnot about my personal struggles because they're quite boring, but just make goddamn sure that you know you are NOT ALONE.

Have a nice life, guys. May the internet and it's diverse culture continue to change, grow, thrive, but most importantly, preserve its roots.

GAME SAVED
JUNE 10, 2020
